<strong>Be bold this summer - stripes are back! And they can be slimming, if you choose well.</strong>

Not sure whether stripes will work with your silhouette?

If you have minimum waist shaping, then either 1 or 4 will look great - the clever geometric designing on 4 creates the illusion of a waist too.

More waisted or curvy? The clever use of thick and thin stripes in this <a title="James Lakeland Striped Dress" href="http://bit.ly/1hLlt6h" target="_blank">James Lakeland dress (3)</a> is perfect and goes up to size 20.

Stripes are great for disguising or enhancing too. The vertical stripes in the skinny trousers will create leg length, whilst the block of colour above the stripes on this linen top from Jaeger can disguise a larger bust. Just make sure that the edge of the sleeve doesn't finish in line with the largest part of the bust.

There's lots more stripes to see! <a title="New Arrivals" href="http://bit.ly/RhXQrU" target="_blank">Take a look now...</a>

